      <article class="story">
        <a id="main-content"></a>
                            <h1 id="page-title" class="title page-title">Contact Us</h1>
                  
                                    
        
        
        
        
        
        
                    <div class="region region-content">
    <div id="block-system-main" class="block block-system">

    
  <div class="content">
    <div id="node-1403" class="node node-page node-promoted full row" about="/contact-us" typeof="sioc:Item foaf:Document">
  <div class="large-12 columns">
            
  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <div class="medium-9 columns">
      <div class="post-body">
      <div class="field field-name-field-image-gallery field-type-image field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"></div></div><div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>WUNC values your feedback. Contact us with and questions, concerns, programming suggestions, or just about anything else related to North Carolina Public Radio:</p> <p>919.445.9150 • 1.800.962.9862 • <a href="mailto:wunc@wunc.org" style="line-height: 1.5;">wunc@wunc.org</a></p> <p>WUNC Radio<br />120 Friday Center Drive<br />Chapel Hill, NC 27517</p>  <p>We have two on-air studios: one in Chapel Hill, one in Durham</p> <ul><li>Goodmon Building<br />120 Friday Center Drive<br />Chapel Hill, NC 27517<br /><iframe frameborder="0" height="300" scrolling="no" src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3231.9210679045614!2d-79.01255379999998!3d35.89994879999999!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x89ace825921c931b%3A0x43f2392ae70c5219!2s120+Friday+Center+Dr!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sus!4v1399913968808" style="border:0" width="89%"></iframe> </li> </ul><ul><li>American Tobacco Historic District Studios:<br />324 Blackwell Street<br />Suite 600<br />Durham, NC 27701-3600<br /><iframe frameborder="0" height="300" scrolling="no" src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m14!1m8!1m3!1d3228.082940083148!2d-78.90516199999999!3d35.99383999999999!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x89ace46cd8d1cf0f%3A0x3e77f6b0383fd15c!2s324+Blackwell+St+%23600!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sus!4v1399914135552" style="border:0" width="89%"></iframe> </li> </ul><p>To contact the <strong style="line-height: 1.5;">newsroom</strong>:</p> <p>Phone: (919) 445-9150 • Fax: (919) 966-5955 • e-mail:<a href="mailto:news@wunc.org">news@wunc.org</a></p>  <p>For questions about<strong> local stories and interviews, </strong>contact WUNC's News Director Brent Wolfe: Phone: (919) 445-9150 • e-mail:<a href="mailto: bwolfe@wunc.org?body=%5Bsend%20from%20wunc.org%5D"> bwolfe@wunc.org</a></p> <p>To call <strong>The State of Things</strong>: 1.877.962.9862 • <a href="mailto:sot@wunc.org?body=%5Bsent%20from%20wunc.org%5D">sot@wunc.org</a></p> <p>To send <strong style="line-height: 1.5;">music CDs to Back Porch Music</strong>:</p> <p>Back Porch Music<br />120 Friday Center Drive<br />Chapel Hill, NC 27517<br />email: <a href="mailto:bpm@wunc.org">bpm@wunc.org</a></p>  <p><a name="onlineform" id="onlineform"></a></p>  <p>For assistance accessing the Online Public File, please contact: <a href="mailto:ncasper@wunc.org?subject=FCC%20Public%20File">Nora Casper</a> at 919-445-9150</p> </div></div></div>      </div>
